place_brief_desc: Narbonne has been an ideal place to stop off when going places since Roman times.
place_longer_desc: Narbonne has been an ideal place to stop off when going places since Roman times as it was where the via Aquitania from the Atlantic via Bordeaux and Toulouse met the via Domitia reaching into Spain. It’s still a great place to change trains when doing the same thing.
